","1283–Male":"1283–Overleden","Abt 1283":"circa 1283","1347":"1347","1323":"1323","1287":"1287","1283":"1283","1318":"1318","1306":"1306","Sweden":"Zweden"},"en":{"Abt 1283–":"about 1283–Deceased","1287–Female":"1287–Deceased","–1347":"–1347","1283–Male":"1283–Deceased","Abt 1283":"about 1283","1347":"1347","1323":"1323","1287":"1287","1283":"1283","1318":"1318","1306":"1306","Sweden":"Sweden","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Birger","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Old Norse: apparently an agent derivative of <i>biarga</i> ‘to help’. Earlier forms of the name are <i>Birghir</i> and <i>Byrghir</i>. It has been in use from the Viking period to the present day, and it may in some cases have been chosen as a masculine form of   Birgit ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Job","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Biblical name, pronounced rhyming with ‘robe’. It is borne in the Bible by the hero of the Book of Job, a man of exemplary patience, whose faith was severely tested by God's apparently motiveless maltreatment of him. His name, appropriately enough, means ‘persecuted’ in Hebrew. His story was a favourite one in the Middle Ages and frequently formed the subject of miracle plays. The name was used among Puritans and Christian fundamentalists, but is currently out of favour, although the form  <b>Jobe</b> , presumably a respelling to fix the pronunciation, is occasionally found."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1702075,"age":23,"year":"1306","julianDay":2198067,"title":"The Hatuna Games","description":"A conflict on September 29, 1306, between Birger, King of Sweden, and his brothers, the dukes Eric Magnusson and Valdemar Magnusson is known as The Hatuna Games. The brothers arrived to a party late in the night at King Birger's estate. The dukes captured and imprisoned Birger and his wife in Nykoping Castle's dungeon. Duke Eric then gained power over Sweden.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1357048,"age":35,"year":"1318","julianDay":2202450,"description":"Peasants revolted against King.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1357049,"age":40,"year":"1323","julianDay":2204276,"description":"Sweden and Russia establish border.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Birger Job was born about 1283, in Sweden. He had at least 1 daughter with Margareta."},"et":{"Abt 1283–":"umbes 1283–Surnud","1287–Female":"1287–Surnud","–1347":"–1347","1283–Male":"1283–Surnud","Abt 1283":"umbes 1283","1347":"1347","1323":"1323","1287":"1287","1283":"1283","1318":"1318","1306":"1306","Sweden":"Rootsi"},"fi":{"Abt 1283–":"noin 1283–Kuollut","1287–Female":"1287–Kuollut","–1347":"–1347","1283–Male":"1283–Kuollut","Abt 1283":"noin 1283","1347":"1347","1323":"1323","1287":"1287","1283":"1283","1318":"1318","1306":"1306","Sweden":"Ruotsi"},"fr":{"Abt 1283–":"environ 1283–Décédé","1287–Female":"1287–Décédée","–1347":"–1347","1283–Male":"1283–Décédé","Abt 1283":"environ 1283","1347":"1347","1323":"1323","1287":"1287","1283":"1283","1318":"1318","1306":"1306","Sweden":"Suède","lifeSummary":"Birger Job est né environ 1283, à Suède. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Margareta."},"de":{"Abt 1283–":"um 1283–Verstorben","1287–Female":"1287–Verstorben","–1347":"–1347","1283–Male":"1283–Verstorben","Abt 1283":"um 1283","1347":"1347","1323":"1323","1287":"1287","1283":"1283","1318":"1318","1306":"1306","Sweden":"Schweden","lifeSummary":"Birger Job wurde um 1283 in Schweden geboren. Er hatte mit Margareta mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"Abt 1283–":"about 1283–Desede","1287–Female":"1287–Desede","–1347":"–1347","1283–Male":"1283–Desede","Abt 1283":"about 1283","1347":"1347","1323":"1323","1287":"1287","1283":"1283","1318":"1318","1306":"1306","Sweden":"Suède"},"hu":{"Abt 1283–":"1283 körül–elhunyt","1287–Female":"1287–elhunyt","–1347":"–1347","1283–Male":"1283–elhunyt","Abt 1283":"1283 körül","1347":"1347","1323":"